Eight points are spaced around at intervals of one unit around a $2 \times 2$ square, as shown. Two of the $8$ points are chosen at random. What is the probability that the two points are one unit apart?\\

\begin{asy}
import olympiad;
import cse5;
defaultpen(white);
size(100);

size((50));
dot((5,0));
dot((5,5));
dot((0,5));
dot((-5,5));
dot((-5,0));
dot((-5,-5));
dot((0,-5));
dot((5,-5));

\end{asy}
\\
\\
$ \textbf{(A)}\ \frac{1}{4}\qquad\textbf{(B)}\ \frac{2}{7}\qquad\textbf{(C)}\ \frac{4}{11}\qquad\textbf{(D)}\ \frac{1}{2}\qquad\textbf{(E)}\ \frac{4}{7} $
